    "system_description": "German disambiguation via case + verb position. Four grammatical cases (nominative, accusative, dative, genitive) encoded in article and adjective endings. Verb-second constraint in main clauses and verb-final in subordinate clauses provides strong positional signal. Together these create two independent disambiguation channels: morphological (case) and positional (verb placement). Critical: German article syncretic forms (der serves nominative masculine, genitive feminine, genitive plural, dative plural) mean case is NOT always unambiguous — verb position becomes the tiebreaker.",
